[thinking] **Clarifying Java Serialization**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m looking into whether the dynamic proxy class extends Proxy and implements Serializable. Yes, it does: `public class Proxy implements java.io.Serializable`. That means the invocation handler can serialize, so even if an interface isn’t serializable, the object can still serialize. It seems a Java dynamic proxy is serializable if its invocation handler is. I guess I'm considering changing the interfaces from Runnable/Serializable to just Cloneable, but I still need to import Serializable for the handler and payload. I might need to rename some things to keep it clear.
